article.description: Shaquille Hines scored 22 points and Texas-Rio Grande Valley snapped a six-game losing streak with a 67-57 upset win over Seattle Thursday night.
article.headline: Texas-Rio Grande Valley upsets Seattle, 67-57 to snap streak
article.linkText: Texas-Rio Grande Valley upsets Seattle, 67-57 to snap streak
article.story: EDINBURG, Texas -- Shaquille Hines scored 22 points and Texas-Rio Grande Valley snapped a six-game losing streak with a 67-57 upset win over Seattle Thursday night. Seattle now has lost back-to-back games after having a five-game win streak snapped. The Redhawks remain in fourth place in the Western Athletic Conference standings, a game ahead of Utah Valley. The Vaqueros started quickly, building a 10-point lead by intermission, 37-27, and matched Seattle point-for-point in the second half. Dan Kimasa and Ot Elmore each added 11 points for Texas-Rio Grande Valley (7-19, 3-8) and Kimasa added 10 rebounds. Jack Crook tied a career high with 22 points, hitting 10 of 15 shots from the field, and grabbed 10 rebounds to lead Seattle (12-13, 6-5). Brendan Westendorf contributed 14 points and William Powell added 10 points and grabbed 13 rebounds.
